# Task API Testing - HTTP Requests
# Use this file with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:8080/actuator/health

### Get all tasks
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tasks

### Create a new task
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "test-001",
  "name": "CI/CD Test Task",
  "owner": "Pipeline Tester",
  "command": "echo Hello from CI/CD Pipeline!"
}

### Get task by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tasks?id=test-001

### Search tasks by name
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/search?name=CI/CD

### Execute task command
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/test-001/execute

### Create another task for testing
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "test-002",
  "name": "Docker Test",
  "owner": "Container Tester",
  "command": "whoami"
}

### Get all tasks (should show both)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tasks

### Delete a task
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/test-001

### Verify deletion
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tasks
